HEADWORD: Stomachous
<hw>Stom"ach*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>stomachosus</ets> angry, peexish. See <er>Stomach</er>.]</ety>
<def>Stout; sullen; obstinate.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With stern looks and <qex>stomachous</qex> disdain.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

